                            <comment id="13583551" author="junrao" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 21:09:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attach a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583555" author="sriramsub" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 21:13:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583582" author="swapnilghike" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 21:55:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583586" author="swapnilghike" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 21:58:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also to maintain consistency with Producer/ConsumerConfigs, perhaps we should verify KafkaConfig properties in the secondary constructor instead of having a separate verify method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583672" author="nehanarkhede" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 23:40:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583938" author="junrao" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2013 05:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review. Committed to 0.8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Swapnil, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree. Could you file a separate jira to track that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584045" author="swapnilghike" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2013 07:16:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-770&quot; title=&quot;KafkaConfig properties should be verified in the constructor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-770&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-770&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277430" author="guozhang" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 18:48:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We encountered a general deaklock issue with System.exit(), where a startup / shutdown aware container wrapping KafkaServerStartable that has shutdown hook executed by another thread is blocked waiting for the main thread in startup() to set the startup_finished flag while the main thread is blocked on waiting for the shutdown hook thread to join.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I would like to propose a bit different solution:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Replace System.exit(1) in startup with the shutdown() call.&lt;br/&gt;
2. In KafkaServer.shutdown, move&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        brokerState.newState(NotRunning)
        shutdownLatch.countDown()
        startupComplete.set(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to the final block.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. Remove the System.exit(1) in shutdown() call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will resolve this issue but as well works with a startup / shutdown aware container that has a shutdown hook depending on the startup logic to be complete.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
